An Uber driver made a quick escape when he was allegedly hijacked and kidnapped by three armed ‘passengers’ on Spine Road, recently. Phoenix communications officer, Captain Louise Naidoo, said: “It is alleged by the victim, an Uber driver that he was contacted to fetch commuters from Spine Road.
On arrival, he picked up three males. Two of them produced firearms and the other a knife. He was instructed to drive toward Ntuzuma. At the robot, he managed to jump off. The vehicle proceeded toward Ntuzuma. The vehicle was recovered later found abandoned at Ntuzuma and taken to the Isipingo pound. No arrests have been made.”
A case of carjacking is under investigation.